   =20
      Citi bonuses
   =20
 =20

I worked at an investment bank during several waves of layoffs, and it alwa=
ys felt odd, because I spent most of my day sitting around with my colleagu=
es complaining about our jobs and fantasizing about quitting. So when layof=
fs would come around we=E2=80=99d all be like =E2=80=9Chow do we get laid o=
ff?=E2=80=9D After all, if you get laid off, you often get a nice severance=
 package, but if you quit you don=E2=80=99t. Of course many of the people w=
ho=C2=A0did=C2=A0get laid off didn=E2=80=99t want to be laid off. They pref=
erred their jobs to the severance package. There were trades to be=C2=A0mad=
e, and it is not unheard-of for investment bankers to volunteer for layoffs=
: If you want to get laid off, and your colleague doesn=E2=80=99t, you can =
make everyone better off by volunteering=C2=A0
Anyway   here=E2=80=99s Citi:

Citigroup Inc. is offering to pay some staffers a portion of their bonuses =
early if they agree to depart as executives continue with their restructuri=
ng of the Wall Street giant.
The bank is making the offer to a limited number of staff, according to peo=
ple familiar with the matter. In addition to the bonus awards, employees wh=
o accept the offer would also be allowed to keep all of their deferred stoc=
k awards, the people said, asking not to be identified discussing personnel=
 information.
Staffers cannot volunteer for the offers because they are being made to tho=
se impacted by Citigroup=E2=80=99s ongoing reorganization, which is focused=
 on restructuring its ranks to fit Chief Executive Officer Jane Fraser=E2=
=80=99s strategy for the bank.

If you get this offer, should you be offended? Does it mean that they=E2=80=
=99d like to get rid of you but wanted to start with a gentle nudge? Or sho=
uld you be thrilled because you get to quit with your bonus?
Also it is mid-December? You have pretty much earned your whole bonus at th=
is point? Sure you get it early by quitting now instead of in March (=E2=80=
=9CCitigroup typically awards staffers their bonuses in February=E2=80=9D),=
 but it=E2=80=99s not=C2=A0that=C2=A0good a deal. Getting half a bonus for =
quitting in May would be an incentive; getting =E2=80=9Ca portion of your b=
onus=E2=80=9D for quitting in December is a little insulting.

